article.description: Cameron Shelton scored 24 points and Bernie Andre added 20 points and seven rebounds as Northern Arizona defeated Idaho State 88-87 in overtime on Thursday night.
article.headline: Shelton scores 24, Andre 20 as NAU defeats Idaho State in OT
article.linkText: Shelton scores 24, Andre 20 as NAU defeats Idaho State in OT
article.story: POCATELLO, Idaho -- Cameron Shelton scored 24 points and Bernie Andre added 20 points and seven rebounds as Northern Arizona defeated Idaho State 88-87 in overtime on Thursday night. Cameron Satterwhite had 19 points and eight rebounds for Northern Arizona (13-8, 7-5 Big Sky Conference). Brooks DeBisschop added 15 points, seven rebounds and three blocks. Shelton's fastbreak layup with one second left in regulation tied the game at 80 and Satterwhite's short jumper with 54 seconds left in the extra period proved to be the game's final points. Neither team led by more than three points after the four-minute mark of the second half and the lead changed hands five times in overtime. Malik Porter had 21 points and Tarik Cool scored 20 for the Bengals (6-15, 3-9), who have lost seven consecutive games. Austin Smellie had 13 points and nine assists. Idaho State defeated Northern Arizona 71-67 on Jan. 11. Northern Arizona plays at Weber State on Saturday. Idaho State plays Sacramento State at home on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- Elements of this story were generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
